15/05/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The country's Council of Ministers on Monday (May 14th) approved an agreement on liberalising the visa regime between the EU and BiH, making it the first country in Southeast Europe to receive such status. The agreement eases restrictions on certain group of citizens such as students and businessmen. 
In other news Monday, BiH and the European Commission officials signed an agreement approving a 2.3m-euro EU donation to the judiciary. The funds will be used to support the work of prosecutors handling war crimes, corruption and organised crime cases. (RTRS, Fena, PBS - 14/05/07)
